==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Illicium
<hw>Il*li"ci*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called, in
allusion to its aroma, from L. <ets>illicium</ets> an allurement.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of Asiatic and American magnoliaceous
trees, having star-shaped fruit; star anise. The fruit of <spn>Illicium
anisatum</spn> is used as a spice in India, and its oil is largely used
in Europe for flavoring cordials, being almost identical with true oil
of anise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Illighten</ent>⟦br⟧
